<subSubSection id="C355652BFFDEE078D746FD84FC72677F" pageId="3" pageNumber="218" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF036A0FFDEE078D746FD84FC72677F" blockId="3.[811,1457,527,1160]" pageId="3" pageNumber="218">
This species is distinguished from the closely related 
<taxonomicName id="4C4F4D23FFDEE078D13CFD84FBC4674A" authority="K. M. Wong &amp; Diep" authorityName="K. M. Wong &amp; Diep" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Bambusa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="218" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gurgandii">
<emphasis id="B93BEAB2FFDEE078D13CFD84FC11674A" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="218">Bambusa gurgandii</emphasis>
K.M.Wong &amp; Diep
</taxonomicName>
by having long internode, blade with non spreading lobe-like auricles, auricles upcurved at the end, 2-4 perfect flowers.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
